stream
BT /F2 21 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 744 Tm (AspieDad Communication Guide) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 726 Tm (A one-page summary with practical communication help for both NT and Aspie readers.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 694 Tm (Research-based framing for spoken communication) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 678 Tm (There is no solid evidence for a universal cutoff like "30 seconds." A better rule is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 664 Tm (keep spoken communication short, manageable, and concrete, one point at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 650 Tm (As a practical starting point, allow at least about 10 seconds before adding more.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 636 Tm (More or less time may be needed depending on the person, stress, environment, and familiarity.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 604 Tm (3 Helpful Tactics For NT Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 586 Tm (1. Be direct and specific.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 572 Tm (Say the real need clearly instead of hinting or expecting it to be inferred.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 554 Tm (2. Use one issue at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 540 Tm (Break information into short, manageable chunks and check understanding before adding more.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 522 Tm (3. Slow down and pause.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 508 Tm (Do not fill silence with more language too quickly. Processing time is often part of understanding.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 476 Tm (3 Helpful Tactics For Aspie Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 458 Tm (1. Say the care out loud.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 444 Tm (Do not assume your love or concern is obvious. NT spouses often need it spoken clearly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 426 Tm (2. Acknowledge feelings before facts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 412 Tm (Start with: "I can see this hurt you" before moving into logic, analysis, or correction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 394 Tm (3. Return after processing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 380 Tm (If you need time, say so directly and come back. Silence without return can feel like rejection.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 348 Tm (3 Simple Phrases For NT Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 332 Tm (1. "I am going to keep this short and clear.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 318 Tm (2. "Can you tell me what you heard me say?") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 304 Tm (3. "We can stay with one issue at a time.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 276 Tm (3 Simple Phrases For Aspie Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 260 Tm (1. "I care about you, even if I am struggling to show it.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 246 Tm (2. "I need a few minutes to process, but I will come back.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 232 Tm (3. "Do you want comfort, help, or for me just to listen?") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 88 Tm (AspieDad.com | Building understanding between NT and Aspie family life) Tj ET
